                    <h4>The main keyword used in eBrickkiln Software which is easy to understand the software working and flow. Because these keywords are commonly used in all state of India.</h4>
                
                    <div class="col-md-11">
                <p><strong>Line type: </strong>In brick kiln business brick are placed inside the kiln or round in shape of line . These lines are in different shape and size so these different lines also known as Pawa type etc.  </p>
                <p><strong>Kachi Bhari: </strong>The process of filling kachi bricks or tiles in the kiln  or in Stock.</p>
                <p><strong>Round /Gher/chakker: </strong>Raw bricks are set up in a circular rows in a kiln. This circular path when meet on starting point is called a 0ne round or Gher.</p>
                <p><strong>Kharaba/Gaal/Wastage: </strong>The total of raw bricks or tiles that are wasted by rain or any other reason.</p>
                <p><strong>Finished Stock: </strong>Stack of baked bricks. Every stack of finished bricks has different grade of bricks. Brick kiln owners keep stack wise stock also.</p>
                <p><strong>Daily: </strong>A document filled by supervisor of brick workers to keep daily record of bricks made by brick workers.</p>
                <p><strong>Pather: </strong>A location where Patheras (Person whose make the raw bricks) molded the bricks.</p>
                <p><strong>Nikashi: </strong>Process to carry out the baked brick or tile from kiln.</p>
                <p><strong>Phukayee/Jalayee: </strong>Process to baking of bricks on daily basis.</p>
                <p><strong>Stack(Chakka or Chatha): </strong>Chatha or chakka is the place where bricks are placed after nikasi. </p>
</div>
